<strong>General Usage:</strong><br/><br/>

1. List all cities in a state<br/><br/>
http://dev.simplerest.com/v1/states/il/cities<br/><br/>

2. List cities within a 100 mile radius of a city<br/><br/>

http://dev.simplerest.com/v1/states/il/cities/chicago?radius=100[&page=1] (using routing done manually)<br/><br/>
or<br/><br/>
http://dev.simplerest.com/v1/states/il/cities/chicago/city?radius=100[&page=1] (using generic routing generated by FOS<br/><br/>


3. Allow a user to update a row of data to indicate they have visited a particular city.<br/><br/>

<strong>POST cURL:</strong><br /><br />

ATTENTION: Content-type: application/json MUST BE PASSED IN THE HEADERS. THERE IS A BUG WITH FOS-BUNDLE-REST<br /><br />

curl -v -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-type: application/json" -X POST -d '{"city": "Chicago","state": "IL"}' http://dev.simplerest.com/v1/users/1/visits<br /><br />

4. Return a list of cities the user has visited<br/><br/>

http://dev.simplerest.com/v1/users/1/visits<br/><br/>

